diction of\ngeneral relativity. At 230 GHz, the n=1 ring is always visible, but the n=2\nring is sometimes suppressed due to absorption. At 345 GHz, the medium is\noptically thinner and the n=2 ring displays clear signatures in both the image\nand visibility domains, identifying this frequency as more promising for future\nspace-VLBI measurements of the photon ring shape.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 Jun 2022 04:16:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Jul 2022 05:35:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-07"}
